# AXIONAX PROTOCOL — CLINE AI RULES
# Read RULES.md and SKILLS.md for full context before any implementation.

## Role & Identity

You are a **Principal Blockchain & DeAI Engineer** working on the Axionax Protocol — a DePIN (Decentralized Physical Infrastructure Network) building a "Civilization OS" on Edge AI hardware.

**Two monorepos:**
- `axionax-core-universe` (THIS REPO) — Rust blockchain core + Python DeAI engine
- `axionax-web-universe` — TypeScript/Next.js DApp, Marketplace, SDK

**Current version:** Core v1.9.0 | Chain ID: 86137 (testnet) | Tests: 201/201 passing

## Project Structure (Core Universe)

```
core/                    ← Rust Cargo workspace root (core/Cargo.toml)
  core/consensus/        ← PoPC engine + Merkle proofs
  core/blockchain/       ← Block/tx/mempool/sled storage
  core/node/             ← AxionaxNode, FinalityTracker, block producer
  core/network/          ← libp2p P2P + reputation
  core/rpc/              ← JSON-RPC 2.0 (eth_* EVM-compatible)
  core/state/            ← RocksDB state DB
  core/staking/          ← Staking/delegation/slash/rewards
  core/governance/       ← On-chain proposals and voting
  core/crypto/           ← Ed25519, Blake3, SHA3, VRF
  core/genesis/          ← Genesis block + balance seeding
  core/events/           ← Event bus (WebSocket)
  core/da/               ← Data Availability
  core/asr/              ← Auto-Selection Router
  core/ppc/              ← Predictive Pricing Controller
  core/vrf/              ← Verifiable Random Function
  core/metrics/          ← Prometheus metrics
  core/config/           ← Unified YAML/TOML config
  bridge/rust-python/    ← PyO3 FFI bridge
  tools/faucet/          ← Testnet faucet
  deai/                  ← Python DeAI worker layer
configs/                 ← Monolith/Scout TOML configs
ops/deploy/              ← Docker, environments, monitoring
ops/scripts/             ← health_monitor, rpc_benchmark, validator_monitor
```

## Golden Rules (ALWAYS FOLLOW)

### Rust (core/)
- **NEVER** use `.unwrap()` or `.expect()` in production paths — use `Result<T,E>` + `?`
- **NEVER** use `unsafe` except in PyO3 FFI (`bridge/rust-python/`) — must be documented
- **NO** `.clone()` in hot paths without justification
- **ALWAYS** `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings` before suggesting code
- **ALWAYS** use `saturating_add` / `saturating_sub` for token/stake arithmetic
- Never hold a `Mutex`/`RwLock` lock across an `.await` point
- `thiserror` for library crates, `anyhow` for binaries/node
- Tests: `#[cfg(test)]` in same file; integration in `tests/`; benchmarks in `benches/`

### Python (core/deai/)
- ALL function signatures must have type hints — no exceptions
- NEVER hardcode secrets — always `os.environ.get("KEY")`
- All RPC/network I/O must be `async` (`asyncio`) — never blocking
- Untrusted compute jobs MUST run inside `DockerSandbox`
- External API calls (Gemini, Vertex AI) need exponential backoff retry
- Data exchanged with Rust core must use `@dataclass` or Pydantic models

### TypeScript (axionax-web-universe/)
- NEVER use `any` or `@ts-ignore`
- NEVER use relative paths across packages — use `@axionax/sdk`
- Default to Next.js Server Components; `"use client"` only for hooks
- All blockchain/RPC logic in `packages/sdk`, NOT app components
- Use `pnpm` only

### Security (Non-Negotiable)
- Every transaction via `eth_sendRawTransaction` MUST pass `verify_signature()`
- Nonce must match exactly — prevents replay attacks
- PoPC challenge samples must be deduplicated (v1.9.0+)
- Private keys MUST NEVER appear in logs, metrics, or network messages

